narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learnt a lot about East Asian archaeology and finding creative ways to research when most publications are in a foreign language.
You learn about the methods/mindset of archaeology while learning about East Asian history/prehistory.
A lot of east Asian archaeology! We cover various regions from China, Japan, Korea, and Cambodia.

how to read archaeological papers and write fair research papers. learned how communities develop over time and how much we can uncover, but also how much is still missing despite archaeological evidence.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The powerpoint presentations are really interesting and discussion is enjoyable if you can follow along with the readings. The readings can be dense, especially if you've never taken an archeology course before, but professor Underhill is so accommodating and happy for any involvement. My favorite part was the last class where everyone shared what their final project/paper was about. It was great!

This class represents the best of Yale. If you want a "fun class that I want explore," this is it. While the class has archaeology majors and grad students, we who've had little to no experience never had to struggle. Learn about archaeology before graduating, it's VERY important! 
The class is not without flaws... mainly, the discussions, which are run by students, aren't always as good... I know I was bad. Maybe in the future, the professor could lead more of the discussions, and students can submit questions in the end.

Strengths: Professor Underhill is extremely nice and really tries to help people learn from all backgrounds of archaeology! Workload is not too much and feedback on essays are very helpful!

Weakness: The readingS sometimes are a bit dense and sometimes gets repetitive.
loved every part of the course. good background with each lecture, and chance to participate the last hour. assignments were minimal which was helpful as other work piled on.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! Professor Underhill is so lovely and you'll learn a lot. Be prepared for a lot of readings that can be confusing, but discussion should help clear up any unclear concepts.
Yes! You must learn about archaeology before graduating, and this class is excellent.
Yes definitely! If you enjoy archaeology this is a great seminar on East Asian archaeology and the discussion are very intriguing!
Totally! great introduction to archaeology and East Asia. lovely professor.
